.TH RUN_SERVER "1" "July 05, 2026" "202607051400-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
run_server \- Start an HTTP server from a directory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B run_server
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,PORT\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B run_server
is a comprehensive script for starting HTTP servers to serve files from a directory. It supports multiple server backends (caddy, nginx, gohttpserver, php, ruby, python, jekyll, rails, etc.) and provides automatic detection of available tools.
.PP
The script includes features for opening browsers, editors, and file managers alongside the server process using GNU screen. It is useful for rapid development, testing, file sharing, and serving static content.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR write
Listen for netcat input and save to file
.TP
.BR static
Start a static file server (tries caddy, php, ruby, python3, then fallback)
.TP
.BR proxy
Setup reverse proxy via caddy
.TP
.BR caddy
Start caddy web server
.TP
.BR go
Start gohttpserver
.TP
.BR jekyll
Start jekyll static site server
.TP
.BR js
Start http-server (Node.js module)
.TP
.BR php
Start PHP built-in server
.TP
.BR rails
Start rails development server
.TP
.BR ruby
Start ruby http.server (WEBrick)
.TP
.BR python2
Start Python 2 http.server
.TP
.BR python3
Start Python 3 http.server
.TP
.BR netcat
Start netcat listener server
.TP
.BR nginx
Start nginx server (same as static)
.TP
.BR default
Try available servers in order (default action)
.SH OPTIONS
.SS "Server Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " \fI\,PATH\/\fR"
Set the working directory to serve files from
.SS "Control Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-bg
Run server in background mode
.TP
.BR \-\-screen
Use GNU screen for window layout management
.TP
.BR \-\-console
Run in console mode
.TP
.BR \-\-silent
Run in silent mode with minimal output
.SS "Browser and Editor Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-browser
Open web browser to access the server
.TP
.BR \-\-editor
Open file editor in editor window
.TP
.BR \-\-filemanager
Open file manager in file manager window
.TP
.BR \-\-enable-browser
Enable browser window on startup
.TP
.BR \-\-enable-editor
Enable editor window on startup
.TP
.BR \-\-enable-filemanager
Enable file manager window on startup
.TP
.BR \-\-enable-all
Enable browser, editor, and file manager on startup
.TP
.BR \-\-disable-browser
Disable browser window
.TP
.BR \-\-disable-editor
Disable editor window
.TP
.BR \-\-disable-filemanager
Disable file manager window
.TP
.BR \-\-disable-all
Disable browser, editor, and file manager
.SS "Utility Options"
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-no-color
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.TP
.BR \-\-allow-root
Allow script to run as root user
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B run_server
Serve current directory on default port
.TP
.B run_server /var/www
Serve /var/www on default port with default server
.TP
.B run_server /var/www python3
Serve /var/www using python3
.TP
.B run_server --dir /var/www --enable-browser python3 8080
Serve /var/www on port 8080, open browser
.TP
.B run_server --screen --enable-all caddy 3000
Serve on port 3000 with screen layout and all auxiliary windows
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/run_server/settings.conf
User configuration file for run_server preferences
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/run_server/
Log directory for server output
.TP
.B ~/.cache/run_server/
Cache directory for temporary files
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUN_SERVER_DEFAULT_PORT
Default port to use if not specified (default: 19922)
.TP
.B RUN_SERVER_DEFAULT_DIR
Default directory to serve (default: $HOME/Public/www)
.TP
.B RUN_SERVER_ENABLE_WEB_BROWSER
Enable web browser window on startup
.TP
.B RUN_SERVER_ENABLE_FILE_EDITOR
Enable file editor window on startup
.TP
.B RUN_SERVER_ENABLE_FILE_MANAGER
Enable file manager window on startup
.TP
.B NO_COLOR
Disable colorized output (ANSI color codes)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or user interrupt
.TP
.B 3
Required command not found
.TP
.B 100
Failed to change directory
.TP
.B 101
Failed to create directory
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Automatically detects and uses available server tools
.IP \(bu 2
Supports multiple server backends for flexibility
.IP \(bu 2
Can integrate with GNU screen for multi-window layout
.IP \(bu 2
Automatically finds free ports if requested port is in use
.IP \(bu 2
Ports below 10000 require root unless --allow-root is specified
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR caddy (1),
.BR nginx (1),
.BR python3 (1),
.BR php (1),
.BR ruby (1),
.BR jekyll (1),
